<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I cannot explain why Fergul would roam about after leaving the fort. As far as aggroing wurms and not the Broodmother, this happens at all times, not exclusive to the quest. The BM doesn't assist other wurms. 

I have also seen all sorts of odd stuff happen with this quest.
The Broodmother never climbs the slope to the fort, she simply wanders about the zone for 20-30 minutes and poofs

The giants despawn, respawn and don't walk out

The quest runs as it should, and then loops. The Broodmother doesn't despawn, and the quest restarts each time Fergul spawns. 

The Broodmother becomes a pet

The Broodmother heads south to Vores the Hunter, and poofs

Fergul's friend doesn't join him outside the fort. Fergul just waits around, and BM never attacks.

All sorts of strange things have happened with this quest. The only beneficial bug Ive experienced was with the quest looping. Managed to get a total of 13 leggings in 2 days over the course of 9 hours.

Things go wrong more often then they go right. The leggings are just slightly worse than EM greaves, and IMO its worth doing the quest over when it breaks.
